{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|くさ}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=くさ|-}}, ultimately from {{inh|ja|jpx-pro|*kusa}}. Found in the ''{{w|Man'yōshū}}'', completed some time after 759 CE.

The development of the {{m|en|fake}}, {{m|en|amateur}} senses is unclear.

{{ja-noun|くさ}}

# [[grass]]
#: {{ja-usex|'''草'''を刈る|'''くさ''' を かる|to cut '''grass'''}}
#: {{synonyms|ja|芝生|tr1=shibafu|q1=in reference to a [[lawn]]}}
# a [[weed]]
# a [[herb]]
#: {{synonyms|ja|ハーブ|tr1=hābu|薬草|tr2=yakusō|q2=medicinal|香草|tr3=kōsō|q3=cooking}}
# a [[scout]], a [[spy]] {{gloss|from the way one would hide in the grass to observe enemy troops}}
# {{lb|ja|sort=くさ|metaphor|slang|rare}} [[pubic hair]]

{{ja-pos|prefix|くさ}}

# a [[fake]], a [[mimic]], not the [[real]] thing
#: {{ja-usex|'''草'''%蜉蝣|'''くさ'''%かげろう|a lacewing fly {{gloss|literally, “'''fake''' or '''mimic''' dragonfly”, from the visual resemblance}}}}
# [[amateur]], [[small-time]]
#: {{ja-usex|'''草'''%野%球、'''草'''%競%馬|'''くさ'''%や%きゅう、'''くさ'''%けい%ば|'''amateur''' or '''pick-up''' baseball, '''small-time''' horse-racing}}

{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|くさ}}

From the resemblance of multiple repetitions of {{m|ja|w|t=[[LOL]]}} to grass: {{lang|ja|wwwwwwwww}}.

Possibly influenced by the term {{ja-r|くすくす}}, an [[adverb]] indicating [[stifled]] [[laughter]]. {{rfv-etymology|ja}}

{{ja-pos|phrase|くさ}}

# {{short for|lang=ja|草生える|tr=kusa haeru|nodot=y}}: {{lb|ja|Internet slang}} &hellip;it's hilarious
#: {{ja-usex|[[鯖]]%落ちて'''草'''|さば% おちて '''くさ'''|'''lol''' the server's down}}
#: {{ja-usex|下手すぎて'''草'''|へた-すぎて '''くさ'''|'''hilariously''' shitty}}
#: {{ja-usex|4日しかないのは'''草'''|よっか しか ない の は '''くさ'''|I've got only 4 days left '''lol'''}}

